Package seng202.team5.accessor

Class RouteAccessor

java.lang.Object
seng202.team5.accessor.RouteAccessor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Accessor
public class RouteAccessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements Accessor
RouteAccessor Contains the functions save, update, delete, getData, and dataExists for routes that directly interact with the database. Implements the Accessor interface.

  • Method Details

    • save

      public int save​(java.util.List<java.lang.Object> data)
      Creates a route in the database with the given data. Requires the airline IATA or ICAO code, airline_id, source airport IATA or ICAO code, source airport_id, destination airport IATA or ICAO code, destination airport_id, codeshare, number of stops, and equipment.
      Specified by:
      save in interface Accessor
      Parameters:
      data - An List containing the data to be inserted into an entry in the database.
      Returns:
      int result The route_id of the route that was just created, -1 if SQL exception occurs.

    • update

      public int update​(int id, java.lang.String newAirline, java.lang.Integer newAirlineID, java.lang.String newSourceAirport, java.lang.Integer newSourceAirportID, java.lang.String newDestAirport, java.lang.Integer newDestAirportID, java.lang.String newCodeshare, java.lang.Integer newStops, java.lang.String newEquipment)
      Updates a given route with new data. Not every field must be updated.
      Parameters:
      id - The route_id of the given route you want to update.
      newAirline - The new 2-letter IATA or 3-letter ICAO code of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newAirlineID - The airline_id of the airline with the given IATA or ICAO code.
      newSourceAirport - The new 3-letter IATA or 4-letter ICAO code of the source airport, may be null if not to be updated.
      newSourceAirportID - The airport_id of the source airline with the given IATA or ICAO code.
      newDestAirport - The new 3-letter IATA or 4-letter ICAO code of the destination airport, may be null if not to be updated.
      newDestAirportID - The airport_id of the destination airline with the given IATA or ICAO code.
      newCodeshare - The new codeshare of the route, "Y" or "N", may be null if not to be updated.
      newStops - The new number of stops for the route, an integer, may be -1 if not to be updated.
      newEquipment - The new equipment for the route, may be null if not to be updated.
      Returns:
      int result The number of rows modified or -1 for error

      public java.sql.ResultSet getData​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> sourceAirport, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> destAirport, int stops, java.lang.String equipment)
      Retrieves all the routes with provided data.
      Parameters:

      destAirport - The 3-letter IATA or 3-letter ICAO code of the destination airport.
